RingoJs
===========

  * Install RingoJs <http://ringojs.org/getting_started>
  * Install packages:

    $ ringo-admin install domasx2/banditracer-client
    $ ringo-admin install domasx2/banditracer-server
    $ ringo-admin install oberhamsi/gamejs
    $ ringo-admin install hns/stick

  * Start http & websocket server:

    $ ringo -e "require('banditracer-server').startUp()"

   * access the Game server at <http://127.0.0.1:8080/>

FIXME: talk about settings-example.js

If you want other's to be able to join your game, they must access the game
with <Your IP:8080> and you must appropriatly set <ws://IP:8787>
in banditracer-client's settings.js!

Node.js
===========

  * Install NodeJs <https://github.com/joyent/node/wiki/Installation>
  * Install <http://npmjs.org/>
  * Install those packages with npm:

  * http://github.com/oberhams/gamejs
  * http://github.com/miksago/node-websocket-server
  * http://github.com/domasx2/banditracer-client
  * http://github.com/domasx2/banditracer-server

Start the websocket server with:

   $ node banditracer-server/nodemain.js

No http server is provided for node, open locally with file://
